      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we plan to use this for compiling crosvm policies at build time, does this API actually expose enough for our use case?\n\nIt will presumably need to run on the build system (in the traditional GNU cross compilation sense, so the system where we are running `cargo build`), which doesn\u0027t necessarily match the architecture or syscall number definitions of the system where crosvm will run. We handle this in the crosvm ebuild by using the Python policy compiler and passing the appropriate board/arch-specific Linux header path, but it doesn\u0027t look like this function can handle cross-compilation.\n\nMaybe that\u0027s OK and we have a different plan for cross-compiled builds?",
      "revId": "3135288dccda0638358eff5ed8c558a98be3b6bf",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
